# Testes Express para Services

## Instanciacao Direta com Mocks

```typescript
describe('RecursoService', () => {
  let service: RecursoService;
  let mockRepository: jest.Mocked<RecursoRepository>;

  beforeEach(() => {
    mockRepository = {
      findMany: jest.fn(),
      findById: jest.fn(),
      create: jest.fn(),
      update: jest.fn(),
      delete: jest.fn(),
    };

    service = new RecursoService(mockRepository);
  });
```

## Testes de Metodos

```typescript
  describe('findOne', () => {
    it('deve retornar recurso quando encontrado', async () => {
      const recurso = { id: '1', nome: 'Teste' };
      mockRepository.findById.mockResolvedValue(recurso);

      const resultado = await service.findOne('1');
      expect(resultado).toEqual(recurso);
      expect(mockRepository.findById).toHaveBeenCalledWith('1');
    });

    it('deve lancar NotFoundError quando nao encontrado', async () => {
      mockRepository.findById.mockResolvedValue(null);

      await expect(service.findOne('999')).rejects.toThrow(NotFoundError);
    });
  });

  describe('create', () => {
    it('deve criar e retornar recurso', async () => {
      const dados = { nome: 'Novo' };
      const criado = { id: '1', ...dados };
      mockRepository.create.mockResolvedValue(criado);

      const resultado = await service.create(dados);
      expect(resultado).toEqual(criado);
      expect(mockRepository.create).toHaveBeenCalledWith(dados);
    });
  });

  describe('update', () => {
    it('deve verificar existencia antes de atualizar', async () => {
      mockRepository.findById.mockResolvedValue(null);

      await expect(service.update('999', { nome: 'X' })).rejects.toThrow(NotFoundError);
      expect(mockRepository.update).not.toHaveBeenCalled();
    });
  });
});
```

## Factory de Dados de Teste

```typescript
function criarRecurso(override: Partial<Recurso> = {}): Recurso {
  return {
    id: '1',
    nome: 'Recurso Padrao',
    criadoEm: new Date('2024-01-01'),
    ...override,
  };
}
```

## Convencoes
- Instanciar service diretamente com `new` — sem framework de DI
- Mockar repositorio via `jest.fn()` no construtor
- Testar cada metodo publico isoladamente
- Testar lancamento de erros de dominio customizados
- Verificar que repositorio nao e chamado em cenarios de erro
- Usar factory functions para dados de teste reutilizaveis
- Sem mocks de Express (service nao conhece HTTP)
{{else}}
# Express Service Testing

## Direct Instantiation with Mocks

```typescript
describe('ResourceService', () => {
  let service: ResourceService;
  let mockRepository: jest.Mocked<ResourceRepository>;

  beforeEach(() => {
    mockRepository = {
      findMany: jest.fn(),
      findById: jest.fn(),
      create: jest.fn(),
      update: jest.fn(),
      delete: jest.fn(),
    };

    service = new ResourceService(mockRepository);
  });
```

## Method Tests

```typescript
  describe('findOne', () => {
    it('should return resource when found', async () => {
      const resource = { id: '1', name: 'Test' };
      mockRepository.findById.mockResolvedValue(resource);

      const result = await service.findOne('1');
      expect(result).toEqual(resource);
      expect(mockRepository.findById).toHaveBeenCalledWith('1');
    });

    it('should throw NotFoundError when not found', async () => {
      mockRepository.findById.mockResolvedValue(null);

      await expect(service.findOne('999')).rejects.toThrow(NotFoundError);
    });
  });

  describe('create', () => {
    it('should create and return resource', async () => {
      const data = { name: 'New' };
      const created = { id: '1', ...data };
      mockRepository.create.mockResolvedValue(created);

      const result = await service.create(data);
      expect(result).toEqual(created);
      expect(mockRepository.create).toHaveBeenCalledWith(data);
    });
  });

  describe('update', () => {
    it('should verify existence before updating', async () => {
      mockRepository.findById.mockResolvedValue(null);

      await expect(service.update('999', { name: 'X' })).rejects.toThrow(NotFoundError);
      expect(mockRepository.update).not.toHaveBeenCalled();
    });
  });
});
```

## Test Data Factory

```typescript
function createResource(override: Partial<Resource> = {}): Resource {
  return {
    id: '1',
    name: 'Default Resource',
    createdAt: new Date('2024-01-01'),
    ...override,
  };
}
```

## Conventions
- Instantiate service directly with `new` — no DI framework
- Mock repository via `jest.fn()` in constructor
- Test each public method in isolation
- Test custom domain error throwing
- Verify repository is not called in error scenarios
- Use factory functions for reusable test data
- No Express mocks (service doesn't know HTTP)
{{/if}}
